gujarati.context:
Here is the translation:

They came with good company everywhere, my loss is not so great; 
Child's fate is tied to old age, they came with foolish people and kept silent.

This is what it says:
"It was said of their own words, many had been satisfied with themselves; 
Then the life-giving breath, having spent a night, has become dawn."

Hate prite jamaadiya jane, shaak paak sundar bhogane;
Pachi aavyo hutashi ni dan, ramya sakhni sanghe bhagvan.

To Him who has been pleased with love and devotion, the most beautiful feast is offered; 
After that, He has come to my door, delighting in the company of devotees, as if it were Bhagavan.

Here is the translation:

After worshipping Hari, one gets filled with devotion; 
daily, one does not see anything but face and takes pleasure in it.

Here is the translation:

Cried Albelo as much as he could, came Maharaja at Gadhde; 
Hears with friends a happy story, cried Rasa and said to shine it.
